                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/887g</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-18T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2882. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1646. Has new agreement with N[etherlands] O[versea] T[rust] been signed by
                    Associated Governments? If not, is it contemplated that War Trade Board should
                    sign joint agreement or separate identic agreement? Clause in general Dutch
                    agreement consenting to N.O.T. agreement removes objection to War Trade Board’s
                    making agreement with N.O.T. similar to that of Associated Governments. Consult
                    with <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_EPL1">Edwards</persName> and repeat
                    this cable to him if he is not at London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
